The church of God, living in exileThe Greek word implies a colony of aliens without full civic rights.
Christians are strangers and pilgrims on earth, their true fatherland being heaven. Cf.
I Peter 2:11;
Phil. 3:20;
Heb. 11:9. in Rome, to the church of God, exiled in Corinth—to you who are called and sanctified by God's will through our Lord Jesus Christ. Abundant grace and peace be yours from God Almighty through Jesus Christ.

4We ask you, Master, be our "helper and defender."Judith 9:11;
Ps. 119:114. Rescue those of our number in distress; raise up the fallen;
assist the needy; heal the sick; turn back those of your people
who stray; feed the hungry; release our captives; revive the
weak; encourage those who lose heart. "Let all the nations
realize that you are the only God,"I Kings 8:60;
II Kings 19:19;
Ezek. 36:23. that Jesus Christ is your
Child, and "that we are your people and the sheep of your
pasture."Ps. 79:13; 95:7; 100:3.

60 You brought into being the everlasting structure of the world by what you did. You, Lord, made the earth. You who are faithful in all generations, righteous in judgment, marvelous in
strength and majesty, wise in creating, prudent in making
creation endure, visibly good, kind to those who trust in you,
"merciful and compassionate,"Joel 2:13;
Sir. 2:11;
II Chron. 30:9.—forgive us our sins, wickedness,
trespasses, and failings.
 2Do not take account of every sin of your slaves and slave girls, but cleanse us with the cleansing
of your truth, and "guide our steps so that we walk with holy
hearts and do what is good and pleasing to you"Ps. 40:2; 119:133;
I Kings 9:4;
Deut. 12:25, 28; 13:18; 21:9. and to our rulers.

3Yes, Master, "turn your radiant face toward us"Ps. 67:1; 80:3, 7, 19;
Num. 6:25, 2. in peace, "for our good,"Gen. 50:20;
Jer. 21:10; 24:6;
Amos 9:4. that we may be shielded "by your powerful


hand"Ex. 6:1;
Deut. 4:34; 5:15;
Jer. 32:21;
Ezek. 20:34. and rescued from every sin "by your uplifted arm."Jer. 32:21;
Ezek. 20:33, 34.
 4Deliver us, too, from all who hate us without good reason. Give
us and all who live on the earth harmony and peace, just as you did to our fathers when they reverently "called upon you in faith and truth."Ps. 145:18;
I Tim. 2:7. And grant that we may be obedient to your almighty and glorious name, and to our rulers and governors on earth.

